    <!-- Chosen Palette: Azure Inspired Neutrals -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A top-down, thematic dashboard design. It starts with a high-level overview (Hero/Stats), moves to competitive analysis (Market Landscape), allows deep exploration (Service Explorer), connects to real-world value (Industry Solutions), and ends with practical adoption info (Ecosystem). This non-linear structure, anchored by a sticky navigation, is chosen for usability, allowing different user personas (executives, developers, students) to enter at their point of interest and explore without being forced through a linear report format. Interactions like tabs and filters manage information density, making a vast topic digestible. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Market Share/Growth: (Goal: Compare) -> Bar Charts (Chart.js). Interaction: Tooltips on hover. Justification: Best for direct, clear comparison of quantitative data between competitors.
        - Global Infrastructure Stats: (Goal: Inform) -> Icon-based stat cards (HTML/CSS). Interaction: Subtle hover animations. Justification: More impactful and scannable than a map or dense text for key metrics.
        - Service Delivery Models: (Goal: Organize) -> 3-column diagram (HTML/CSS Flexbox). Interaction: Hover highlight. Justification: Visually represents the hierarchical IaaS/PaaS/SaaS relationship more effectively than a list.
        - Service Portfolio: (Goal: Organize) -> Tabbed interface (JS). Interaction: Click to switch categories. Justification: Manages the complexity of 600+ services by grouping them thematically, preventing information overload.
        - Keystone Technologies: (Goal: Inform/Organize) -> Modal pop-ups with HTML/CSS diagrams. Interaction: Click to view details. Justification: Allows for a "deep dive" on critical services without cluttering the main interface.
        - Industry Use Cases: (Goal: Organize/Inform) -> Filterable card grid (JS). Interaction: Click industry buttons to filter. Justification: Provides tailored information relevant to a user's specific domain.
        - Certification Paths: (Goal: Organize) -> HTML Table. Interaction: Row hover highlight. Justification: The most structured and readable format for presenting the relationship between roles and certifications.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
